Class PersonRecord

  • java.lang.Object
    • PersonRecord

  • public class PersonRecord
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is responsible for holding the data entered for the current record and formattig said data. It also keeps track of the number of entries that have been entered.

        public java.lang.String formatName(java.lang.String names)

        Local variables:

        name3 - String which holds the new name with only the good and formatted elements

      • formatPhone

        public java.lang.String formatPhone(java.lang.String phone)
        This is the method used to format the user input for their phone number. It inserts a dash after 3 numbers and then again after another 3.

        Local variables:

        tempStr - String which holds only the digits of the user input

        i - integer which keeps track of the for loop to check each character and only adds digits to the tempStr

        Parameters:
        phone - A String used to pass the phone number to be formatted into the method.
        Returns:
        returns the phone number formatted with dashes
